Newsom answers question on why he's not wearing a face covering at press briefings 1 / 3 Back to GalleryAt a Friday briefing, California Gov.
Gavin Newsom was asked why he doesn't wear a face covering in his daily press conferences.
While the governor has yet to issue an official order requiring residents to wear face masks, he has repeatedly encouraged people to use them in public situations where social distancing isn't possible.